00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:49,840
 to believe this towards the end.

545
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:53,600
 That contentment is not found in better circumstances,

546
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:58,400
 it is found in a deeper closeness to Christ.

547
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,080
 And that's what the Apostle Paul is

548
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:03,580
 going to try to show us in Philippians chapter 4,

549
00:20:03,580 --> 00:20:05,880
 starting in verse 10.

550
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:08,400
 This is what it says.

551
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:12,360
 Paul says, "I rejoiced in the Lord greatly,

552
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:16,000
 because once again you renewed your care for me.

553
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,160
 You were in fact concerned about me,

554
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:20,720
 but lacked the opportunity to show it.

555
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:23,600
 And I don't say this out of need,

556
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:27,120
 for I have learned to be content in whatever circumstances

557
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:28,440
 I find myself.

558
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:31,520
 I know both how to make do with little,

559
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:33,760
 and I know how to make do with a lot,

560
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:35,960
 in any and all circumstances."

561
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:36,480
 I love this.

562
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:40,280
 "I have learned the secret of being content,

563
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:43,000
 whether well-fed or hungry, whether in abundance

564
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:43,960
 or in need."

565
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,400
 Verse 13.

566
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:50,600
 "I am able to do all things through Him who strengthens me."

567
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:53,240
 And then skip down to verse 19.

568
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:59,600
 He ends it with this, "And my God will supply all your needs

569
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:05,200
 according to His riches in glory in Christ Jesus."

570
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:07,840
 Tonight, here's what I want to focus on.

571
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:09,760
 If you're going to give the message a title,

572
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:12,520
 it's just "The Lie of More."

573
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:14,600
 Because I think one of the greatest threats

574
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:17,920
 to our contentment as we journey through life

575
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:22,280
 is the lie that more is what you and I need,

576
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:23,560
 that we need more.

577
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:24,640
 We need more attention.

578
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:25,640
 We need more money.

579
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:28,800
 We need more romance, more success, more freedom,

580
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:30,640
 more control.

581
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:33,960
 But Paul is leaning in tonight and speaking to you and I,

582
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:37,680
 and he says, "I've learned that in whatever situation

583
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:41,040
 that I'm in, that I can be content."

584
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:48,320
 In other words, I'm learning something deeper than more.

585
00:21:48,320 --> 00:21:50,080
 I'm learning something deeper than more.

586
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:52,360
 So if you're taking notes tonight,

587
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:56,200
 here's point number one, that the world in which we live

588
00:21:56,200 --> 00:22:00,120
 is shaping us, whether you believe this or not,

589
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:02,680
 towards discontentment.

590
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:06,400
 That's like the default setting of our culture.

591
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,480
 And if you don't believe me, let me just give you

592
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:09,520
 a couple of examples.

593
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:11,480
 And I want to start here before we do,

594
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:13,680
 because I believe that many of us

595
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:18,680
 underestimate how this is actually shaping our day to day.

596
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:25,360
 For example, ads, commercials, Instagram sponsored,

597
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:28,040
 like whatever, like all of those.

598
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:33,440
 One of the core messages in every single one of them

599
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:37,360
 is having to sow seeds of discontentment in your heart

600
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:38,600
 for it to work.

601
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:41,840
 The ad does not work if you're not discontent.

602
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:46,480
 And so ads are not selling you products,

603
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:51,160
 they're selling you a vision for the good life.

604
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:53,440
 They're not selling you shoes, they're

605
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:55,560
 selling you significance.

606
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:57,480
 They're not selling you skin care,

607
00:22:57,480 --> 00:23:00,360
 they're selling you confidence.

608
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:02,200
 They're not selling you a vacation,

609
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:05,800
 they're selling you an escape.

610
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:12,000
 Now listen, I'm not anti-ads, I'm not anti-marketing,

611
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,720
 I don't think it's all evil.

612
00:23:14,720 --> 00:23:18,680
 I'm just saying that almost every commercial and all

613
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:22,000
 of advertising that the number one principle in play

614
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:25,520
 is feeding off of your discontentment,

615
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:30,360
 awakening the sense of lack in you.

616
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:34,120
 And that there's this gap between where you are

617
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:36,240
 and where you should be.

618
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:38,720
 Or maybe there's a gap between what you have

619
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:41,920
 and what you need, or a gap between who you are

620
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:42,920
 and who you could be.

621
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,440
 And this is important, and I don't want you to miss this.

622
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:48,600
 If we're not careful that you and I,

623
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:54,120
 we start using that same exact logic in our relationship

624
00:23:54,120 --> 00:23:55,360
 with God.

625
00:23:55,360 --> 00:24:00,520
 We start assuming that if God was really good,

626
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:04,400
 then life would look different than it does now.

627
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:06,800
 If God was really kind, then that door

628
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:09,440
 would have opened by now.

629
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:13,760
 If God was really faithful, I wouldn't feel so behind

630
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:16,160
 in life.

631
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:19,040
 And I want you to hear me.

632
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:23,320
 The desires of your heart are rarely the problem.

633
00:24:23,320 --> 00:24:30,360
 It's not wrong to want to be married.

634
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:33,400
 It's not wrong to want more meaningful work.

635
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:35,920
 It's not wrong for you to want a healing,

636
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:39,000
 or do you want more friendships?

637
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:42,520
 A lot of those are good desires.

638
00:24:42,520 --> 00:24:49,840
 The problem is when desire slowly becomes distrust.

639
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:52,080
 When your desires slowly become distrust,

640
00:24:52,080 --> 00:24:55,360
 then what we want starts rewriting

641
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:58,040
 what we believe about God.

642
00:24:58,040 --> 00:25:01,560
 When our longings start to turn into quiet resentments

643
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:05,000
 toward God, or maybe when it's that ache that

644
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:09,840
 starts to whisper to our heart, maybe, just maybe,

645
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:15,360
 God's holding out on you, that He's forgotten you.

646
00:25:15,360 --> 00:25:16,040
 He's missed you.

647
00:25:16,040 --> 00:25:18,200
 He doesn't care.

648
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:20,880
 And don't miss this.

649
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:24,480
 That's not a new lie.

650
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:27,640
 It's a very, very old lie.

651
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:30,960
 If you just want to go back to page 3 of the scripture

652
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:34,560
 in Genesis, the enemy's strategy in the garden

653
00:25:34,560 --> 00:25:37,280
 is not just rebellion.

654
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:39,960
 It was discontentment.

655
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:42,760
 That's where it started, that he plants suspicion

656
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:44,240
 in the hearts of Adam and Eve.

657
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:48,320
 Did God really say this?

658
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:51,240
 Can God really be trusted?

659
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:54,400
 Is He really good?

660
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:57,600
 God's holding out on you.

661
00:25:57,600 --> 00:26:00,360
 It's the same lie.

662
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:03,560
 And suddenly, Adam and Eve, surrounded

663
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:07,760
 by the goodness of God, start fixating on the one thing

664
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:10,760
 in their life that they're missing.

665
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:12,680
 And I want you to watch this.

666
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:17,680
 That's the pattern of discontentment in our hearts,

667
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:22,200
 that we go blind to the thousands of yeses

668
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:24,640
 that God has given us.

669
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:29,000
 Adam and Eve, thousands of yeses, thousands of trees

670
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,720
 to pick from the garden, thousands of ways

671
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:34,240
 to be satisfied and complete and content.

672
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:38,080
 And the enemy shows up and goes, but let's focus on the one

673
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:40,040
 no.

674
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:41,960
 Let's focus on the one thing that you

675
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:47,880
 feel like you're missing, so that you miss out on the life

676
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:50,320
 that God is offering.

677
00:26:50,320 --> 00:26:54,040
 And that's why this is so dangerous.

678
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:56,400
 This isn't just a pep talk.

679
00:26:56,400 --> 00:27:01,600
 This discontentment has the ability to completely erode.

680
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:06,600
 Your joy and your relationship with Christ.

681
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:10,040
 It takes a life full of grace, and it turns it

682
00:27:10,040 --> 00:27:11,640
 into a list of what's missing.

683
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:19,480
 And here we are, thousands of years later,

684
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:25,000
 and that ancient lie just has better branding now.

685
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:28,920
 It now comes with filters and sponsored content.

686
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:32,080
 It comes with a comparison that fits in your pocket,

687
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:35,560
 and it comes with an algorithm that knows exactly where

688
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:39,240
 you're most vulnerable.

689
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:42,320
 And it keeps preaching the same sermon.

690
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:44,040
 You need more.

691
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:45,800
 You're missing out.

692
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:48,880
 You should be further now.

693
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:51,160
 And Paul, in verse 11, what he says

694
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:57,560
 is he says, I've learned in whatever situation that I'm in,

695
00:27:57,560 --> 00:28:00,160
 I am to be content.

696
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:02,200
 Which here's the good news.

697
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:08,040
 This means that contentment is possible even in a world that

698
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:11,360
 profits off your restlessness.

699
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:14,240
 So that leads us to the main focus of this message

700
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:16,120
 and point number two, and here it is.

701
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:19,560
 Contentment is learned in Christ.

702
00:28:19,560 --> 00:28:22,680
 So yes, we see that we live in a world that's naturally

703
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,680
 pushing us towards discontentment.

704
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:28,000
 But here Paul's going to tell us that contentment is learned

705
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:29,920
 in Christ.

706
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:31,080
 And I love that.

707
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:33,240
 I love that word learned.

708
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:34,960
 Because watch this.

709
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:39,600
 Paul does not say that I was born content.

710
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:41,800
 I was born content.

711
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:45,160
 No, and he doesn't say that the moment that I met Jesus,

712
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:47,880
 that I stopped struggling with contentment.

713
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:49,200
 No.

714
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:52,000
 He doesn't say that contentment came easy for him.

715
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:54,720
 He says, I learned it.

716
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:55,440
 I learned it.

717
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:57,840
 And that means contentment usually--

718
00:28:57,840 --> 00:29:01,240
 don't miss it-- doesn't come naturally.

719
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:04,400
 It's not our default setting.

720
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:05,240
 It's formed.

721
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:06,120
 It's forged.

722
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:08,000
 It's fought for.

723
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:11,440
 But that's actually really good news, Porch.

724
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:16,080
 Because if it can be learned, then it can be taught.

725
00:29:16,080 --> 00:29:17,000
 It can be grasped.

726
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,920
 It's something within our reach.

727
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:22,920
 And it means that contentment's not just for the spiritual

728
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:25,320
 superheroes.

729
00:29:25,320 --> 00:29:29,480
 Contentment's not reserved for monks or missionaries

730
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:34,120
 or people who journal with cool calligraphy pens.

731
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:38,800
 It means that contentment can be learned by normal people

732
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:41,680
 like you and I.

733
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:49,960
 And Paul says, he says, I know how to make do with a little.

734
00:29:49,960 --> 00:29:52,440
 I know how to make do with a lot.

735
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:53,600
 What he's saying is this.

736
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:56,680
 He says, hey, on all sides of the spectrum, I've lived.

737
00:29:56,680 --> 00:30:00,280
 Like, I know what it's like to live in a pithouse.

738
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:05,400
 And I also know what it's like to sleep on prison floors.

739
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:10,400
 I know what it's like to be able to buy all of my friends

740
00:30:10,400 --> 00:30:12,000
 a meal at a nice restaurant.

741
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:15,960
 But I also know what it's like to live off ramen noodles.

742
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:19,080
 Like, I know what it's like to live with open doors.

743
00:30:19,080 --> 00:30:21,200
 And I know what it's like to live in prison cells.

744
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:23,800
 I know what it's like to have experienced ease.

745
00:30:23,800 --> 00:30:26,960
 And I know what it's like to experience suffering.

746
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:30,280
 And somewhere in the middle of all of that,

747
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:31,600
 I learned a secret.

748
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:38,840
 And that secret is contentment in Christ.

749
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:42,120
 That's where it's found.

750
00:30:42,120 --> 00:30:46,080
 Which, what I hope, is that tonight there

751
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:48,040
 would be some part of you that would

752
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:51,040
 want to lean in to the invitation

753
00:30:51,040 --> 00:30:55,520
 that the Apostle Paul is extending to you and I.

754
00:30:55,520 --> 00:31:02,440
 To go, Paul, if that's true, I need to know.

755
00:31:02,440 --> 00:31:09,840
 Paul, if that's legit, I need you to show me how this works.

756
00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:13,680
 Before we do that, I want to just highlight a few things

757
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:16,960
 that contentment is not.

758
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:22,600
 And the first is this, that contentment is not comfort.

759
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:24,120
 Contentment is not comfort.

760
00:31:24,120 --> 00:31:28,520
 Paul is writing this letter to his friends

761
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:33,040
 that are part of the family of God while he's in prison.

762
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:35,200
 He's saying, I've learned the secret

763
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,520
 of what it means to be content.

764
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:40,120
 And he's content while being shackled in a prison cell.

765
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:41,320
 So he's not at a beach.

766
00:31:41,320 --> 00:31:43,840
 He's not in a cabin in the mountains.

767
00:31:43,840 --> 00:31:46,680
 He's not on some season where everything's finally

768
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:47,840
 working in his favor.

769
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:49,600
 He's in chains.

770
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:52,600
 So therefore, contentment cannot mean ease.

771
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,000
 It cannot mean convenience.

772
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:57,760
 It can't mean the absence of pain.

773
00:31:57,760 --> 00:32:01,960
 Which means contentment is-- watch this-- not pretending

774
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:03,280
 like life doesn't hurt.

775
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:09,760
 Like your contentment is not pretending or putting

776
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,280
 on a show for everyone around you

777
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:13,800
 that life is just hunky dory.

778
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:17,200
 It's not faking a smile through disappointment.

779
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:18,880
 It's not spiritual denial.

780
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:22,200
 It's not saying everything's fine when everything

781
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:26,280
 is very much not fine.

782
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:28,840
 And I think, listen, just as a sidebar,

783
00:32:28,840 --> 00:32:30,720
 I don't know how many of you guys are single.

784
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,760
 I was single until I was 30.

785
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:35,840
 And I remember one of the number one bit of advice

786
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:39,720
 that I would hear in the church world towards single people

787
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:41,160
 was it was some form of this.

788
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:44,800
 It was like, hey, as soon as you get content,

789
00:32:44,800 --> 00:32:46,240
 as soon as you get content, God's

790
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:49,200
 going to bring you a spouse.

791
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:51,240
 And so what it created in our church--

792
00:32:51,240 --> 00:32:52,200
 probably not here at the porch.

793
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:52,700
 I don't know.

794
00:32:52,700 --> 00:32:55,160
 But at our church, it was just a bunch of single people

795
00:32:55,160 --> 00:32:57,560
 walking around just going, God, I'm so content.

796
00:32:57,560 --> 00:33:01,960
 Where is she?

797
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:05,040
 Where is she?

798
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:07,240
 And so it just caused a bunch of us

799
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:11,320
 to pretend, to put on a show, and act

800
00:33:11,320 --> 00:33:14,640
 like we weren't really affected.

801
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:17,200
 And I don't know if you find yourself

802
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:21,960
 in that performative nature, but that's not contentment.

803
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:26,120
 Contentment is not pretending you don't feel the ache.

804
00:33:26,120 --> 00:33:30,760
 It is the settled confidence that Christ is enough

805
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:34,320
 in the middle of the ache.

806
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:39,200
 Second, contentment is not complacency.

807
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:41,360
 I think that a huge fear for many of us

808
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:44,200
 is that we think that the moment that we get content where

809
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:46,560
 we are currently in our life, that moment

810
00:33:46,560 --> 00:33:50,760
 that we get content, God's just going to leave us there.

811
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:55,280
 And one, that's just not who God is.

812
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:56,840
 So contentment does not mean that you

813
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:58,280
 stop wanting good things.

814
00:33:58,280 --> 00:34:00,200
 It doesn't mean that you don't stop praying

815
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:01,800
 or that you stop growing.

816
00:34:01,800 --> 00:34:02,440
 You can listen.

817
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:02,940
 Hear me.

818
00:34:02,940 --> 00:34:08,400
 You can still want marriage and be content in singleness.

819
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:10,320
 It's a radical idea.

820
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:13,400
 And listen, tonight, I'm about to just free some of you.

821
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,640
 Two things can be true--

822
00:34:15,640 --> 00:34:18,040
 that you can still pray for a healing

823
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:21,680
 while being content in weakness.

824
00:34:21,680 --> 00:34:24,320
 That you can still pursue growth and be

825
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:27,040
 content with where you are.

826
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:32,760
 Contentment is not the death of your desires.

827
00:34:32,760 --> 00:34:35,720
 It's surrendering the demand that life

828
00:34:35,720 --> 00:34:41,880
 must happen on your timeline in order for God to be good.

829
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:44,160
 Contentment is surrendering the demand

830
00:34:44,160 --> 00:34:48,080
 that life must happen on your timeline in order for God

831
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:50,640
 to be good.

832
00:34:50,640 --> 00:34:54,880
 The third thing that contentment is not

833
00:34:54,880 --> 00:34:58,200
 is that it's not circumstantial.

834
00:34:58,200 --> 00:35:00,920
 And this one is massive.

835
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:04,600
 And so I'm just going to speak from my heart tonight.

836
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:07,200
 But Paul is illustrating through this scripture here.

837
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:09,520
 He's saying that my circumstances--

838
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:12,520
 that there are things around me.

839
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:15,600
 There are the things that are changing around me.

840
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:20,280
 But my contentment is not built on what surrounds me.

841
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:23,440
 It's built on who sustains me.

842
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:24,640
 And I want you to hear this.

843
00:35:24,640 --> 00:35:27,880
 That's a massive difference, that our contentment is found

844
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:31,660
 in who holds us, not in the circumstance that surround us.

845
00:35:31,660 --> 00:35:35,880
 Because if your peace, if your contentment,

846
00:35:35,880 --> 00:35:41,760
 is built on your circumstances, then all of it will be fragile.

847
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:43,880
 Because jobs change.

848
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:45,000
 People leave.

849
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:46,080
 Money fluctuates.

850
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:47,480
 Bodies break down.

851
00:35:47,480 --> 00:35:48,520
 Doors close.

852
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:50,120
 Dreams get delayed.

853
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:53,680
 If your contentment is built on things that move,

854
00:35:53,680 --> 00:35:57,000
 then your soul will move with them.

855
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:59,400
 So let me say it this way.

856
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:05,200
 Contentment is not a condition around you.

857
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:07,800
 It's a condition within you.

858
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:13,600
 And I know that this may seem very obvious,

859
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:15,840
 but I want to explain it this way.

860
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:19,880
 And I love you enough to tell you this.

861
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:24,720
 That right now, if you step into this room,

862
00:36:24,720 --> 00:36:26,420
 and if you were to be honest with me--

863
00:36:26,420 --> 00:36:28,200
 and I know church is not really a place to be honest.

864
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:28,960
 It's where we pretend.

865
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:30,880
 But just let's break that wall and just

866
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:33,160
 pretend that we're going to be honest with each other.

867
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:35,960
 And I would ask you, how are you doing?

868
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:37,720
 And tonight, if you were to be honest and be

869
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:39,480
 like, yeah, I feel I'm discontent

870
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:42,320
 in this stage of my life, whatever it may be.

871
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,900
 I thought that I'd be married by now.

872
00:36:43,900 --> 00:36:45,480
 I thought maybe I'd have kids by now.

873
00:36:45,480 --> 00:36:48,680
 And I feel discontent with this.

874
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:51,560
 And I love you enough to tell you this.

875
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:53,060
 And you're not going to believe me,

876
00:36:53,060 --> 00:36:56,600
 but I'm going to try my best anyway.

877
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:58,600
 That right now, if you are discontent

878
00:36:58,600 --> 00:37:03,320
 with your singleness, I will promise you

879
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:06,160
 that you will carry every bit of that discontentment

880
00:37:06,160 --> 00:37:09,520
 into your marriage.

881
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:11,360
 And then all of that discontentment

882
00:37:11,360 --> 00:37:15,940
 will follow you into your parenting.

883
00:37:15,940 --> 00:37:19,560
 If you're discontent in your job right now,

884
00:37:19,560 --> 00:37:21,640
 it will follow you to your next job.

885
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:28,240
 And maybe now more than ever, we have built up

886
00:37:28,240 --> 00:37:32,760
 a generation that is constantly discontent with every situation

887
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:36,320
 and we just find ourselves chasing thing after thing

888
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:37,760
 to find out that discontentment's

889
00:37:37,760 --> 00:37:39,600
 at the bottom of all of it.

890
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:42,440
 Because watch this, discontentment is not

891
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:43,960
 about your circumstance.

892
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:46,200
 You're not discontent because you're single.

893
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:48,920
 You're not discontent because of the job that you have.

894
00:37:48,920 --> 00:37:52,840
 Discontentment is a heart condition

895
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:57,560
 that's been a part of the human journey since page 3.

896
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:05,280
 And it's found its way all the way to 2026.

897
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:08,200
 So I know that it's hard to believe because every one of you

898
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:10,840
 are like, Drew, no.

899
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:16,760
 The moment that I get married, it'll be gone.

900
00:38:16,760 --> 00:38:21,760
 And can I just say this as a way of illustration?

901
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:27,920
 If you're in this space and you know Jesus,

902
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:31,320
 like you have a relationship with him, like you would say,

903
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:32,680
 yes, Drew, I know him.

904
00:38:32,680 --> 00:38:33,480
 I love him.

905
00:38:33,480 --> 00:38:36,280
 I'm not just like playing the game, like actually know him.

906
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:38,120
 Then let me kind of just explain it this way.

907
00:38:38,120 --> 00:38:41,720
 You are already in a relationship.

908
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:45,600
 And if that relationship does not satisfy you,

909
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:50,040
 what makes you think that some broken woman or some broken man

910
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:52,600
 will somehow be able to do what Jesus can't do in your life?

911
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:59,760
 You're already in a relationship.

912
00:38:59,760 --> 00:39:01,360
 So what you're saying is, no, no, no.

913
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:03,280
 Like what I need is I need more relationships.

914
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:04,680
 Then I would be happy.

915
00:39:04,680 --> 00:39:05,720
 I need more money.

916
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:06,960
 Then I'd be happy.

917
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:07,680
 I need more.

918
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:08,280
 I need more.

919
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:11,240
 I need more of all the things that already don't satisfy me.

920
00:39:11,240 --> 00:39:12,640
 And if I get more of those things,

921
00:39:12,640 --> 00:39:16,240
 then somehow I think that maybe they'll satisfy me.

922
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:18,640
 And it doesn't work.

923
00:39:18,640 --> 00:39:22,000
 And it's a lie that plugs us into the matrix

924
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:25,400
 and just lets us live with the illusion.

925
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:26,800
 Isn't that the big meme right now?

926
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:29,280
 It's like the big joke is that all of adulting

927
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:32,000
 is just saying, it's a season until you die.

928
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:38,520
 That's our culture's way of kind of like poking to the matrix.

929
00:39:38,520 --> 00:39:40,800
 And it's like, ah, I think we just say,

930
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:44,800
 I'm discontent until I die.

931
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:47,520
 And contentment is--

932
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:51,160
 it's not about your circumstances.

933
00:39:51,160 --> 00:39:53,600
 It's about your heart.

934
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:57,000
 And that's why Paul, he shifts the gears.

935
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:57,880
 And he's going to go.

936
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:59,380
 This is where he's going to go next.

937
00:39:59,380 --> 00:40:08,680
 And so in verse 13, he says, "I can do all things through Him

938
00:40:08,680 --> 00:40:11,320
 who strengthens me."

939
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:12,480
 Now pause.

940
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:16,080
 This is one of the most quoted and most misunderstood verses

941
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:18,120
 in the entire scripture.

942
00:40:18,120 --> 00:40:19,680
 We put it on coffee mugs.

943
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:21,320
 Athletes ride it on their tennis shoes.

944
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:23,720
 People quote it before big job interviews, or CrossFit

945
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:25,320
 workouts, or leg day.

946
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:28,760
 Now listen, I'm not mad about it.

947
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:32,840
 I'm just saying that's not what Paul is talking about.

948
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:37,480
 Paul is not saying that Jesus helps me crush my goals.

949
00:40:37,480 --> 00:40:41,360
 All of this, Philippians 4, 13, "I

950
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:44,000
 can do all things through Christ who strengthens me."

951
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:46,880
 All of that is built around the context

952
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:49,500
 or in the context of contentment.

953
00:40:49,500 --> 00:40:54,680
 He's saying, listen, I can endure the lack of all things

954
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:58,160
 through Christ because He's what sustains me.

955
00:40:58,160 --> 00:41:01,920
 I can endure abundance and overflow through Christ

956
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:05,080
 because He holds my heart, not my circumstances.

957
00:41:05,080 --> 00:41:08,080
 I can walk through disappointment through Christ.

958
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:09,640
 I can suffer through Christ.

959
00:41:09,640 --> 00:41:17,080
 I remain steady no matter what happens around me

960
00:41:17,080 --> 00:41:20,160
 through Christ.

961
00:41:20,160 --> 00:41:24,760
 Paul is not saying that Jesus makes me impressive.

962
00:41:24,760 --> 00:41:28,800
 Paul is saying that Jesus makes me steady.

963
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:30,240
 And I think that's what some of us

964
00:41:30,240 --> 00:41:33,480
 need tonight because I think a lot of us

965
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:37,200
 are asking Jesus to make us impressive,

966
00:41:37,200 --> 00:41:41,400
 make me more successful, make me more visible,

967
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:45,800
 make me more admired, make me more accomplished.

968
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:52,160
 And Jesus is saying, I'm not trying to make you impressive.

969
00:41:52,160 --> 00:41:54,960
 I'm trying to make you anchored.

970
00:41:54,960 --> 00:41:56,560
 I'm trying to make you rooted.

971
00:41:56,560 --> 00:42:01,640
 I'm trying to make you steady because a steady soul in Christ

972
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:04,440
 is worth more than a spectacular life without Him.

973
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:13,000
 And Jesus is inviting you and I into something so much bigger

974
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:17,440
 than just a fancy life with more.

975
00:42:17,440 --> 00:42:20,080
 He's inviting us into a world that

976
00:42:20,080 --> 00:42:22,640
 is steady no matter what storm comes our way,

977
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:26,160
 no matter what circumstances are thrown, that you and I will

978
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:29,080
 be able to go, no, I'm content.

979
00:42:29,080 --> 00:42:35,080
 That I'm trusting God with what He's doing right now.

980
00:42:35,080 --> 00:42:37,360
 Because a steady soul, like I said, is more spectacular.

981
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:40,720
 Paul says the secret is not self-sufficiency.

982
00:42:40,720 --> 00:42:43,400
 It's Christ-sufficiency.

983
00:42:43,400 --> 00:42:45,480
 That Christ in me gives me strength

984
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:48,440
 for what life is doing around me.

985
00:42:48,440 --> 00:42:50,240
 That when the outside world is unstable,

986
00:42:50,240 --> 00:42:56,040
 I can have stability on the inside because Jesus is near.

987
00:42:56,040 --> 00:42:58,760
 So I just want to kind of land the plane tonight.

988
00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:03,720
 And I want to ask you this.

989
00:43:06,440 --> 00:43:12,400
 What are you asking circumstances

990
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:19,680
 to do that only Christ can do for you?

991
00:43:19,680 --> 00:43:23,000
 What are you asking a relationship to do for you

992
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:26,760
 that only Christ can do for you?

993
00:43:26,760 --> 00:43:28,600
 What are you asking a paycheck to do

994
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:33,920
 that only Christ can do for you, a future to do for you?

995
00:43:33,920 --> 00:43:41,040
 Because if you put ultimate weight on temporary things,

996
00:43:41,040 --> 00:43:46,480
 hear me, they will crush you.

997
00:43:46,480 --> 00:43:48,680
 They'll crush you.

998
00:43:48,680 --> 00:43:53,360
 Because only Jesus can hold the weight of your soul.

999
00:43:53,360 --> 00:43:54,680
 The secret's not more.

1000
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:56,720
 The secret is Christ.

1001
00:43:56,720 --> 00:43:59,560
 And so there's a lot more that I would

1002
00:43:59,560 --> 00:44:01,040
 love to share with you tonight.

1003
00:44:01,040 --> 00:44:06,840
 But I just kind of want to wrap it up with this.

1004
00:44:06,840 --> 00:44:11,400
 In my 20-year journey with Jesus,

1005
00:44:11,400 --> 00:44:17,600
 it has been only in the last maybe three years

1006
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:19,720
 that I've started to actually really lean into this.

1007
00:44:19,720 --> 00:44:22,280
 Because listen, I'm giving you a cautionary tale.

1008
00:44:22,280 --> 00:44:25,880
 I can say with confidence that I carried my discontentment

1009
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:30,800
 into my marriage because I was discontent with my singleness.

1010
00:44:30,800 --> 00:44:34,040
 I can tell you that that's been my story

1011
00:44:34,040 --> 00:44:37,720
 for a majority of my life.

1012
00:44:37,720 --> 00:44:40,320
 And even as a pastor, it has only

1013
00:44:40,320 --> 00:44:42,400
 been in the last two or three years

1014
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:44,480
 that I've kind of come to this place

1015
00:44:44,480 --> 00:44:49,400
 where I'm starting to realize that Paul's words are true.

1016
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:50,200
 And here's why.

1017
00:44:53,560 --> 00:45:02,120
 Because this thing with Jesus, it's not like a relationship.

1018
00:45:02,120 --> 00:45:06,320
 It is a relationship.

1019
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:09,000
 And that subtle difference has started to make

1020
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:12,160
 a huge change in my own heart.

1021
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:15,520
 As I've started to realize that this relationship with Jesus,

1022
00:45:15,520 --> 00:45:17,440
 that's not a metaphor.

1023
00:45:17,440 --> 00:45:19,280
 That's not an analogy that we try

1024
00:45:19,280 --> 00:45:22,280
 to help us make sense of this big spiritual cosmos.

1025
00:45:22,280 --> 00:45:24,880
 No, no, it's not like a relationship.

1026
00:45:24,880 --> 00:45:26,160
 It is a relationship.

1027
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:31,760
 That Jesus is inviting you and I into intimacy with him,

1028
00:45:31,760 --> 00:45:35,080
 to walk with him, to wrestle with him,

1029
00:45:35,080 --> 00:45:37,640
 to share the things that we're really going through.

1030
00:45:37,640 --> 00:45:42,000
 To go, God, listen, I really, really desire a new job.

1031
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:44,160
 Or I really desire to be married.

1032
00:45:44,160 --> 00:45:46,560
 Or I thought that I'd have kids by now.

1033
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:52,800
 But I trust you.

1034
00:45:52,800 --> 00:45:56,240
 I trust you.

1035
00:45:56,240 --> 00:46:08,280
 Because of the heart behind all of our discontentment

1036
00:46:08,280 --> 00:46:08,960
 is distrust.

1037
00:46:08,960 --> 00:46:14,920
 That, God, I think you're holding out on me.

1038
00:46:14,920 --> 00:46:19,880
 That every bit of your discontentment

1039
00:46:19,880 --> 00:46:23,160
 with where you are in the journey right now

1040
00:46:23,160 --> 00:46:28,720
 exposes that underneath what's really going on,

1041
00:46:28,720 --> 00:46:31,000
 you go, God, you missed me.

1042
00:46:31,000 --> 00:46:37,400
 I don't think you're actually good.

1043
00:46:37,400 --> 00:46:39,360
 I don't know if you love me.

1044
00:46:39,360 --> 00:46:48,040
 And I think the secret is in verse 9, 19.

1045
00:46:48,040 --> 00:46:53,800
 When Paul says this, he says, "My God."

1046
00:46:53,800 --> 00:47:01,480
 He says, "My God will supply all your needs."

1047
00:47:01,480 --> 00:47:05,280
 There's intimacy there.

1048
00:47:05,280 --> 00:47:10,000
 There's this familiarity there.

1049
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:12,560
 Paul's not just talking about a distant deity.

1050
00:47:15,480 --> 00:47:20,560
 He says, "My God can be trusted."

1051
00:47:20,560 --> 00:47:22,520
 And my God's a really good father.

1052
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:30,120
 I think I shared this story with Watermark not too long ago,

1053
00:47:30,120 --> 00:47:32,080
 but I think it's worth repeating.

1054
00:47:32,080 --> 00:47:38,200
 My daughter Tilly is just--

1055
00:47:38,200 --> 00:47:41,280
 I mean, she really is just a magical little human,

1056
00:47:41,280 --> 00:47:42,880
 seven-year-old.

1057
00:47:42,880 --> 00:47:44,840
 And she just has this ability to see people.

1058
00:47:44,840 --> 00:47:47,120
 And if you were to come over to our house in San Antonio

1059
00:47:47,120 --> 00:47:51,600
 and hang out with her, maybe play, like, Barbies,

1060
00:47:51,600 --> 00:47:54,160
 or she just, like, is constantly looking for, like, your needs.

1061
00:47:54,160 --> 00:47:55,600
 And so she might see that you're hungry.

1062
00:47:55,600 --> 00:47:57,080
 She's like, "Ah, I got fruit snacks."

1063
00:47:57,080 --> 00:47:58,840
 She'll just give them to you.

1064
00:47:58,840 --> 00:48:01,360
 But if you spend the afternoon playing,

1065
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:03,080
 and you're going to leave our house,

1066
00:48:03,080 --> 00:48:05,680
 and we give you the goodbyes, and you walk out,

1067
00:48:05,680 --> 00:48:07,800
 and Tilly noticed that you had a really good time

1068
00:48:07,800 --> 00:48:09,400
 playing with her, she'll run up to you,

1069
00:48:09,400 --> 00:48:13,960
 and she'll give you one of her Barbies.

1070
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:15,840
 And it's happened enough to where

1071
00:48:15,840 --> 00:48:17,120
 we've had this conversation.

1072
00:48:17,120 --> 00:48:18,280
 We have to pull Tilly aside.

1073
00:48:18,280 --> 00:48:21,840
 I'm like, "Hey, sissy, like, give all the fruit snacks

1074
00:48:21,840 --> 00:48:22,600
 you want away.

1075
00:48:22,600 --> 00:48:23,840
 Those are super cheap.

1076
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:32,840
 But Barbies are expensive, so let's hold on to those, OK?"

1077
00:48:32,840 --> 00:48:39,560
 And true story, Tilly's response was, "Dad,

1078
00:48:39,560 --> 00:48:41,160
 you can always buy me more."

1079
00:48:44,480 --> 00:48:51,720
 Which I thought was cute, until I felt like the Lord just

1080
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:52,560
 shared this with me.

1081
00:48:52,560 --> 00:49:01,840
 As broken and as sinful as I am, my daughter

1082
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:05,560
 is growing up in a home where she

1083
00:49:05,560 --> 00:49:12,080
 knows that she has a daddy that loves her and sees her.

1084
00:49:14,920 --> 00:49:20,440
 And not for one minute has ever let her go without.

1085
00:49:20,440 --> 00:49:22,840
 And that she can live a life of contentment

1086
00:49:22,840 --> 00:49:24,320
 with Barbies, without Barbies.

1087
00:49:24,320 --> 00:49:24,840
 Why?

1088
00:49:24,840 --> 00:49:30,920
 Because daddy's always going to take care of me tonight.

1089
00:49:30,920 --> 00:49:40,800
 Is that the God that you know or claim to know?

1090
00:49:40,800 --> 00:49:43,360
 Because what Paul's inviting you and I into

1091
00:49:43,360 --> 00:49:49,080
 is that we have a daddy who loves us, who sees us.

1092
00:49:49,080 --> 00:49:52,200
 There's never, ever been a moment in your life

1093
00:49:52,200 --> 00:49:54,160
 that he's missed you, that you've gone without,

1094
00:49:54,160 --> 00:49:55,840
 that he hasn't wanted to take care of you,

1095
00:49:55,840 --> 00:50:00,320
 and that he gives good gifts in his timing.

1096
00:50:00,320 --> 00:50:05,040
 And if we don't have it now, it may be his loving kindness

1097
00:50:05,040 --> 00:50:09,000
 that says, "You're just not ready."

1098
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:13,720
 Or, "I want to use this season for something else."

1099
00:50:13,720 --> 00:50:16,320
 I know I've been using the example of singleness a lot,

1100
00:50:16,320 --> 00:50:18,280
 but I think sometimes it's the most applicable.

1101
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:18,800
 Why?

1102
00:50:18,800 --> 00:50:22,320
 Because listen, many of you, that's the season

1103
00:50:22,320 --> 00:50:23,720
 that you're walking in.

1104
00:50:23,720 --> 00:50:27,040
 That's the season that you find the most discontentment

1105
00:50:27,040 --> 00:50:27,760
 in your heart.

1106
00:50:27,760 --> 00:50:35,240
 And God may be going, "This is a season like no other season

1107
00:50:35,240 --> 00:50:39,280
 before or after where you'll get to love me, and serve me,

1108
00:50:39,280 --> 00:50:42,400
 and do my will like it is right now."

1109
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:45,640
 When you get married, it's going to be a little bit different.

1110
00:50:45,640 --> 00:50:53,000
 But tonight, we can go on so many adventures together.

1111
00:50:53,000 --> 00:50:55,960
 May you not wish that away.

1112
00:50:55,960 --> 00:51:02,400
 May you trust that whatever season you're in right now,

1113
00:51:02,400 --> 00:51:07,960
 he sees you, he knows you, he cares,

1114
00:51:07,960 --> 00:51:11,520
 he's not leaving you there.

1115
00:51:11,520 --> 00:51:14,600
 But it will take trust.

1116
00:51:14,600 --> 00:51:20,160
 And it won't always be easy, but he's good,

1117
00:51:20,160 --> 00:51:22,880
 and he's always been good.

1118
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:28,240
 So Jesus, tonight I pray that we fill that invitation.

1119
00:51:31,840 --> 00:51:36,280
 For our lives to be completely centered around you,

1120
00:51:36,280 --> 00:51:38,680
 and not the circumstances in our world,

1121
00:51:38,680 --> 00:51:41,360
 or not the things that we hope would shift or change.

1122
00:51:41,360 --> 00:51:45,520
 But Jesus, that you, that we would see you as the treasure

1123
00:51:45,520 --> 00:51:47,720
 that you promise that you are.

1124
00:51:47,720 --> 00:51:55,760
 That we would, we'd find so much contentment in your presence.

1125
00:51:55,760 --> 00:51:58,960
 Not because we're pretending, just because we're close to you

1126
00:51:58,960 --> 00:52:01,880
 and it's real and it's true.

1127
00:52:01,880 --> 00:52:09,160
 So Jesus, tonight, just open our eyes.

1128
00:52:09,160 --> 00:52:11,320
 And to see you, to be captured by you.

1129
00:52:11,320 --> 00:52:18,560
 Father, I feel so limited tonight.

1130
00:52:18,560 --> 00:52:27,920
 And so I'm just asking you to do what only you can do.

1131
00:52:29,960 --> 00:52:36,960
 And speak to your people, invite us into more,

1132
00:52:36,960 --> 00:52:39,920
 more of you, and more of your presence.

1133
00:52:39,920 --> 00:52:46,800
 And may tonight we leave forever changed.

1134
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:49,880
 Not because of anything that was mentioned from this stage,

1135
00:52:49,880 --> 00:52:53,760
 but because you spoke.

1136
00:52:57,560 --> 00:52:59,560
 We love you.

